# gjoa-patch:
#   baseline-firefox: 152.0
#   touches:
#     - servo/components/style/values/specified/color.rs
#     - servo/components/style/device/gecko.rs
#     - layout/base/nsPresContext.h
#     - layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp
#     - dom/chrome-webidl/BrowsingContext.webidl
#     - docshell/base/BrowsingContext.h
#     - docshell/base/BrowsingContext.cpp
#
Engine-level dark mode: luminance-invert resolved absolute colors at
style-resolution time (the performant successor to the compositor filter:invert).

- specified/color.rs: invert_color_luminance() ports gfx RelativeLuminanceUtils
  ::Adjust (WCAG, hue/sat/alpha-preserving) with target = 1 - luminance. Applied
  at the END of Color::to_computed_color so it covers EVERY resolved absolute
  color — explicit colors, resolved color-functions, AND system colors (so the
  page Canvas/default background goes dark under force-light, not just explicit
  colors). currentColor / color-mix / unresolved color-functions stay symbolic
  and resolve against the already-inverted values. Cached in ComputedValues ->
  zero per-frame cost; raster media untouched.
- device/gecko.rs: color_inversion() accessor (mirrors forced_colors()).
- nsPresContext.{h,cpp}: per-document mColorInversion flag + UpdateColorInversion
  (content-only; chrome excluded), called at construction and on change of the
  gjoa.darkmode.invert.enabled pref (live toggle via RecascadeSubtree).

The "engine" dark-mode mode (src/gjoa chrome) forces prefers-color-scheme:light
then flips this flag, so sites render light and the engine inverts to dark.

